history.content:
@3831

Particularly in Item 3: "The instructor is likely to speak briefly during the first lecture about discussion section attendance.  "  = "It's up to the professor."

I am now successfully enrolled for CS170, with the generic discussion section. I read the related threads, and I think there is nothing else I can do online to choose a specific discussion section of my liking. Would like some confirmation on that.

In that case, how will my discussion section be eventually determined ? I show up in a section, on the day, and see if I am allowed in ? There is no priority number for discussion section for me, except for priority number of the generic section that I got into, which I have no way of knowing now. So, how will my discussion section of choice be filled up from all the people whose first choice is that discussion section ?
history.subject: my preference for a specific discussion section of CS170
